title: UWF women’s soccer team shuts out Mississippi College
text:
UWF women’s soccer team shuts out Mississippi College From staff reports, pnj.com 9:32 p.m. CDT October 25, 2015 UWF women's soccer coach Joe Bartlinski takes team on pair of road games this weekend in GSC play. (Photo: Ben Twingley/btwingley@pnj.com) CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
The University of West Florida women’s soccer team improved its record to 11-4 overall and 7-3 in the Gulf South Conference with a 2-0 win over Mississippi College on Sunday. 
UWF notched a shutout for the seventh time this season and outscored opponents this weekend 7-0. This was just the third time this season that the Choctaws have been held without a goal. 
Daryl Bell got the offense moving with a goal in the 22nd minute of the first half, and she struck against less than 90 seconds later with her 10th goal of the year. Sara Helgadottir was credited with her third assist of the season on Bell’s first goal, and Kaley Ward chipped in with her fourth assist this year on Bell’s second goal. 
Bell becomes just the second player in the GSC with 10 goals on the year. The win moves UWF into fifth place overall in the GSC standings and into fourth among teams eligible for the postseason. 
UWF will travel to Valdosta State for a GSC match on Wednesday before hosting West Georgia in the team’s regular-season finale on Saturday. 
VSU sits at 3-6-1 in conference play, while West Georgia stands just behind UWF at 6-3-1. Read or Share this story: http://on.pnj.com/1N1B4Sy TOP VIDEOS
